results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 LV8 GS ‘Year of the Tiger’ showcases unique details in celebration of Chinese New Year. The low-top carries an off-white canvas upper with a striped Swoosh in University Gold. An embroidered tiger head graphic adorns the lateral heel, while the woven tongue tag displays the Chinese character for ‘king,’ referencing the tiger’s standing as the king of all beasts. The low-top is mounted on a solid white midsole, featuring Air-sole cushioning in the heel and an orange rubber outsole underfoot.

results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Air More Uptempo ‘96 GS ‘Split’ features mismatched branding that honors Scottie Pippen, the athlete who wore the shoe during the Bulls’ fourth championship season and with Team USA during the squad’s gold medal run at the Atlanta Olympics. The twin achievements are reflected in the signature ‘AIR’ logo that adorns the black nubuck upper, featuring red lettering on the lateral side and navy lettering on the opposite side. The sneaker lives up to its billing with visible Air-sole cushioning, while the salute to Pippen is made complete with his personal logo added to the heel tab.

results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low GS ‘Pink Velvet’ carries a leather upper that pairs a clean white base with soft pink overlays. The latter hue is repeated on the plush textile lining and velvet heel tab, branded with an embroidered Nike wordmark in red lettering. Additional crimson accents land on the sneaker’s woven tongue tag and sockliner. The retro silhouette is mounted on a white rubber midsole, supported underfoot by a lightly speckled pink rubber made with 15% Nike Grind.

results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Blazer Mid '77 SE GS ‘White Rush Maroon’ takes the retro silhouette from the hardwood to the dance floor. Inspired by ‘everything dance,’ the redesigned upper features a grey suede base with white leather paneling and a reinforced toe. A stitched Swoosh on the medial side is complemented by a cropped maroon leather Swoosh on the opposite side. Additional branding elements include an embroidered Nike wordmark on the heel tab and ‘Just Do It’ inscribed on a pull loop atop the tongue. Underfoot, a maroon herringbone rubber outsole yields grippy traction.

results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Air Force 1 GS ‘Toasty’ updates the classic silhouette with a winter-ready build made with 20% recycled content by weight. The color-blocked upper features a warm fleece-lined interior and quilted textile paneling in white, Oil Green, Medium Olive and Sequoia. Nike’s pinwheel logo decorates the woven tongue tag, while an embroidered Swoosh graces the pink synthetic suede heel tab. The low-top rests on a solid white rubber cupsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Georgetown (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low GS ‘Georgetown’ pays homage to the Hoyas with a familiar two-tone palette laid out in classic ‘Be True to Your School’ color blocking. The retro hoops shoe employs a leather upper that pairs a light grey base with contrasting overlays in Dark Obsidian. A lone pop of contrasting color is revealed inside the shoe, via Nike branding stamped in Total Orange on the sockliner. The low-top rests on a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring clean white sidewalls with a dark navy rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Test of Time Sail Green (GS)
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 LV8 GS ‘Test of Time’ features a vintage look that nods to the silhouette’s long-standing appeal as a wardrobe staple. The upper is constructed from off-white suede with a green hairy suede Swoosh, appended with a yellow Nike tag on the lateral side. Inside the shoe, a custom sockliner is inscribed with the phrase ‘Standing the test of time.’ The sneaker sits atop a cream-colored rubber cupsole, fitted with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel.

results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low SE GS ‘Black Light Photo Blue Mint Foam’ combines heritage style with sustainable materials. White laces secure the all-leather upper, featuring a solid black base with contrasting blue overlays and a mint green Swoosh. Speckled detailing distinguishes the heel tab, marked with a playful Nike logo in fuchsia-colored block letters. Multicolored speckling is repeated on a grippy rubber outsole made in part with Nike Grind.

Nike Dunk Low Retro NN Toasty Sequoia (GS)
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Dunk Low SE Next Nature GS ‘Toasty’ reimagines the ‘80s hoops shoe with a winter-ready build that incorporates 20% recycled content by weight. Quilted textile in Sequoia is utilized on the upper, featuring tonal synthetic leather overlays and a contrasting orange Swoosh. A Nike wordmark is embroidered on the heel tab, while the brand’s retro pinwheel logo adorns the woven tongue tag. The sneaker sits atop a two-tone rubber cupsole made in part with Nike Grind.

results.name: Nike Zoom Freak 3 Clear Emerald (GS)
results.story: The Nike Zoom Freak 3 GS ‘Clear Emerald’ gives big kids the chance to lace up a vibrant colorway of Giannis Antetokounmpo’s third signature shoe. The upper is constructed from turquoise-colored textile and secured with a combination of standard laces and an adjustable hook-and-loop strap. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a springy foam midsole with a TPU wing embedded in the lateral sidewall for added support. Underfoot, a camo-like print in black and green suffuses a rubber outsole with a split in between the forefoot and heel for improved flexibility.

results.name: Nike LeBron 19 Dutch Blue Lime Glow (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike LeBron 19 GS ‘Tropical’ updates LeBron James’ signature shoe with vibrant accents. White semi-translucent textile is utilized on the upper, equipped with a stretchy interior sleeve and a webbing pull tab at the heel. Neon green laces are fed through blue TPU wings that wrap up the sides of the foot for improved containment. The Cushlon midsole features responsive Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot with a 360-degree Max Air unit under the heel.

results.name: Nike LeBron 19 Bred (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike LeBron 19 GS ‘Bred’ treats LeBron James’ signature shoe to a classic two-tone color scheme. The upper is constructed from black translucent textile with molded TPU wings for enhanced support around the midfoot and collar. Interior bootie construction, alongside crimson Flywire cables, delivers a snug, locked-in fit. The sneaker rides on a hybrid cushioning setup that pairs a responsive Zoom Air unit in the forefoot with a dual-chambered Max Air bag under the heel. Underfoot, a decoupled red rubber outsole yields flexible traction on the hardwood.

results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low Premium GS ‘Halloween’ gets in the holiday spirit with hidden glow-in-the-dark graphics. They cover the sneaker’s black leather overlays, contrasted by an off-white leather base and a synthetic leather Swoosh in Starfish orange. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole is similarly treated to a luminescent finish. Branding elements include a debossed Nike wordmark on the black-out leather heel tab and tongue tag. Atop the orange sockliner, a spider graphic accompanies a classic Nike logo.

results.story: Built for big kids, the NBA x Nike Dunk Low EMB GS ‘Spurs’ is taken from a footwear collection celebrating the league’s 75th Anniversary, aka the diamond anniversary. A matte black finish is executed on the leather upper, fortified with tonal tumbled leather overlays and accented with a metallic silver Swoosh. Standard Nike branding hits atop the tongue and heel tab are by joined silver lace jewels stamped with a diamond graphic. A rubber cupsole anchors the low-top, featuring crisp white sidewalls and a black rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low EMB NBA 75th Anniversary Chicago (GS)
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the NBA x Nike Dunk Low EMB GS ‘Bulls’ is taken from a special collection celebrating the league’s 75th anniversary. This pair pays homage to Chicago, featuring an off-white leather upper with contrasting tumbled leather overlays in crimson and black. A commemorative 75th anniversary tongue tag displays Jerry West’s iconic silhouette from the NBA logo, while a diamond graphic is stamped on the metallic lace jewel as a nod to the league’s diamond anniversary. The sneaker is finished with standard cupsole tooling, comprising a white midsole and red rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 NBA 75th Anniversary Trail Blazers (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids and included in a footwear collection celebrating the league’s 75th anniversary, the NBA x Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 LV8 EMB GS ‘Trail Blazers’ features a familiar palette inspired by Portland. The low-top carries a tumbled black leather upper with mismatched accents: the lateral side pairs a Chile Red Swoosh with a quarter panel in Grey Fog, while the medial side flips the contrasting colors. Unique branding hits include a 75th anniversary tongue tag and an embroidered mini-Swoosh in red, grey and black on the heel tab. Underpinning the sneaker is an off-white rubber midsole with contrast red stitching and a hidden Air-sole unit in the heel.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low EMB NBA 75th Anniversary Fiesta (GS)
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the NBA x Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 LV8 EMB GS ‘Spurs’ recognizes the league’s 75th anniversary with a retro ‘90s palette inspired by San Antonio’s championship franchise. The vintage hoops shoe carries a white tumbled leather upper with light grey quarter panels and mismatched Swooshes in turquoise and Sundial. A woven 75th anniversary tag adorns the tongue, while an embroidered mini-Swoosh in blue, black and hot pink graces the heel tab. The sneaker rests on a crisp white rubber midsole, accented with contrast turquoise stitching and enhanced with hidden Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low EMB NBA 75th Anniversary Brooklyn Nets (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the NBA x Nike Dunk Low EMB GS ‘Nets’ showcases a throwback color scheme celebrating the league’s 75th anniversary, aka the diamond anniversary. The leather upper references the Nets’ time in New Jersey, featuring a light grey base with tumbled leather overlays in white and Blue Void, while a graphic on the lateral heel nods to the franchise’s current home in Brooklyn. Unique branding elements include a 75th anniversary tongue tag and a diamond graphic etched on metallic sliver lace dubrae. A contrasting pop of color arrives via red stitching on the white midsole, supported underfoot by a navy rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Championship Navy (PS)
results.story: The Nike Dunk High PS ‘Midnight Navy’ brings back an OG colorway in little kid sizing. Originally made for Villanova University as part of the 1985 ‘Be True to Your School’ series, the vintage hoops shoe features an all-leather upper that combines a pristine white base with contrasting navy overlays. The sneaker is equipped with a padded textile-lined collar and a breathable nylon tongue embellished with a woven Nike tag. A durable rubber cupsole anchors the high-top, featuring a solid white midsole and navy rubber outsole.

results.story: The Nike Zoom Freak 3 GS ‘Digital’ treats the bid kids’ edition of Giannis Antetokounmpo’s third signature shoe to a computerized makeover. Secured with a fuchsia-colored midfoot strap, the black textile upper is accented with a reverse neon green Swoosh and a pink grid-like pattern around the collar. The right tongue features Giannis’ personal logo, while the left displays an ‘Input Data’ command. The sneaker rides on a sculpted foam midsole with a stabilizing TPU wing embedded in the lateral sidewall. Underfoot, the two-tone rubber outsole is enhanced with a computer-generated traction pattern that resembles a topographical map.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Social Status Free Lunch Strawberry Milk (PS)
results.story: Made for little kids, the Social Status x Nike Dunk Low PS ‘Strawberry Milk’ showcases a unique design inspired by the public school system’s free lunch program. Varying shades of pink are executed on an upper that combines a nubuck base with velvet construction on the collar, eyestay and forefoot overlay. A TPU gel Swoosh cuts across the side panels, while mismatched Tyvek tongue tags display Nike and Social Status branding. Printed text on the medial heel lists the sneaker’s ‘ingredients.’ The low-top rests on an off-white midsole, supported underfoot by an olive green rubber outsole.

results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Kyrie 7 GS ‘1 World 1 People’ treats Kyrie Irving’s signature shoe to a vibrant makeover. Mismatched hues distinguish the sneaker’s TPU forefoot fins, featuring embossed graphics that include a peace sign and Kyrie’s All-Seeing Eye. ‘1 World 1 People’ is inscribed in black lettering across the heel overlay. A soft foam midsole gives way to a two-tone rubber outsole equipped with a 360-degree data-inspired traction pattern.

The two-tone palette up top is repeated on the sneaker’s cupsole tooling, which pairs a white midsole with a navy-colored rubber outsole.
